<HL>
   Who's News:
   Student Loan Marketing Association
</HL>
<DATE>
05/22/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4
</SO>
<CO>
   WNEWS SLM
</CO>
<LP>
   STUDENT LOAN MARKETING ASSOCIATION (Washington) -- Timothy
G. Greene was named executive vice president and general
counsel of this operator of a secondary market in educational
loans. Mr. Greene, 51 years old, a Dallas lawyer who was
Sallie Mae's first general counsel, will succeed Ronald F.
Hunt, 47, who will begin a law practice in North Carolina in
midsummer. Among the challenges Mr. Greene will face is a
legal battle with commercial banks over Sallie Mae's right to
originate student loans.
</LP>
